. ( ) (The Hon. Rauff Hakeem, Attorney-at-Law) Hon. Speaker, I am also a Member of that Committee. Yesterday also I pointed out that with this deal, there is a serious implication for the country. I talked, in my speech yesterday, about the drop in tourist arrivals, that when you compare the tourist arrivals in the country duing the period of the first three months of this year with that of last year, a heavy drop has been observed. I questioned the Sri Lanka Tourism Development Authoritys Director General at a meeting of the Committee on Public Finance. I showed him the graph and the details, and he agreed before the Committee that this drop is because of this new visa fiasco. This is causing severe stress economically for the country and ultimately, that is what is going to happen. We have also agreed with the IMF to have a Governance Diagnostic Assessment of our Government's activities. This is a serious violation of procurement procedures and therefore, this is going to impact even on the IMF programme. That is what I see. I have also annexed a separate report with some details, which I have taken up at the Committee. Ultimately, the amount of money that will be transferred to this new entity after 16 years is almost US Dollars 2.65 billion, and this is going to result in a serious violation of financial discipline in the country.

Therefore, this has to be thoroughly probed without waiting for the so-called forensic report from the Auditor-General. Now, this is a property of the House. Sir, it has been presented to you and you are the Speaker. You can invite the Attorney-General to examine this and refer it to the Criminal Investigation Department or the Commission to Investigate Allegations of Bribery or Corruption because this has serious implications. I dare say that this is 10 times more than the Central Bank bond scam. That is my estimation and I take responsibility for what I am saying. Some of our Hon. Members are also looking at other options, but I would invite your attention to this, Hon. Speaker, because this has a serious implication for the country. Therefore, this must be referred to the Attorney-General, the CID and the Commission to Investigate Allegations of Bribery or Corruption to go into the background regarding this matter.
Thank you. ) ( () ) (The Hon. (Dr.) Harsha de Silva) , . .
